Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js Pages Router

Summary:
Successfully installed and configured @vercel/speed-insights package for this Next.js project using the Pages Router architecture.

Changes Made:
1. Installed @vercel/speed-insights package (v1.3.1) using npm
2. Modified pages/_app.js:
   - Added import statement: import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'
   - Added <SpeedInsights /> component inside the NextUIProvider wrapper
   - Placed after {Component} to ensure proper rendering order

Files Modified:
- package.json - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- package-lock.json - Updated lockfile with new dependency tree
- pages/_app.js - Integrated SpeedInsights component

Implementation Details:
- Used Pages Router configuration since the project uses pages/_app.js (not App Router)
- Imported from '@vercel/speed-insights/next' which is the correct path for Pages Router
- Component is automatically configured and will work once deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration needed - SpeedInsights will automatically track page navigation

Testing:
✓ Build completed successfully with no errors
✓ Linting passed during build process
✓ All static pages generated correctly (8/8)
✓ No TypeScript or runtime errors introduced

The Speed Insights will start collecting performance metrics once the application is deployed to Vercel.
